Access Meetup events using a group, member, or event id

API Description

Provider

Meetup

Decription

Meetup is an online social networking portal that facilitates offline group meetings in various localities around the world. Meetup allows members to find and join groups unified by a common interest, such as politics, books, games, movies, health, pets, careers or hobbies.

URL

http://www.meetup.com/meetup_api/

Twitter

https://twitter.com/Meetup

Github

https://github.com/meetup

OpenAPI

https://raw.githubusercontent.com/streamdata-gallery-master/streamrank/master/_listings/meetup/findtopics-get-openapi.md

Curl command through Streamdata.io

curl -v "https://streamdata.motwin.net/http://api.meetup.com2/events?X-Sd-Token={streamdata_token}&event_id={field_value}&fields={field_value}&group_domain={field_value}&group_id={field_value}&group_urlname={field_value}&limited_events={field_value}&member_id={field_value}&rsvp={field_value}&status={field_value}&text_format={field_value}&time={field_value}&venue_id={field_value}"
